Several states are concerned about the costly and privacy-invading new driver's license rules proposed by Rep. James Sensenbrenner.
Mike Huckabee and others are ready to fight against these rules, which they believe are anti-immigrant.
Immigrant rights groups argue that the rules won't enhance security but will harm immigrant communities.
Critics fear the creation of a national ID card and increased hostility towards foreign-born residents.
The proposed legislation aims to prevent terrorism but faces opposition from various groups.
The bill could lead to chaos at motor vehicle bureaus and impact the Latino community negatively.
